{
  "number": 790,
  "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/issues/790",
  "title": "urlSync bug with base attribute",
  "body": "Hello,\n\nThere is a bug happening when `urlSync: true` and the html page has a `base` attribute which is different from the current URL. It will instantly replace the URL with the `base` url, to which is appended the instantsearch.js state as a query string\n\nDemo: http://url-syncbug.surge.sh/test\n\nThe base attribute is: \n\n``` html\n<base href=\"http://url-syncbug.surge.sh\">\n```\n\nThe page URL is instantly changed to http://url-syncbug.surge.sh/?q=rake&hPP=6&idx=Version_development&p=0&is_v=1\n\nOne solution could be to replace the entire URI path instead of just the query params part\n",
  "created_at": "2016-01-22T15:10:51Z",
